# Testing

Use Vitest through Vite+: `import { … } from "vite-plus/test"` (never `vitest` directly). Run with `vp test` / `npm test`. Coverage gate: `npm run test:coverage` (min **80%** lines/functions/branches/statements on domain + application + registry adapters; see `apps/web/vite.config.ts`).

Colocate domain/application tests next to use cases. Prefer fake ports over mocking D1 adapters.

## Pyramid

1. Domain + pure policies (no I/O)
2. Application use cases with fake ports (`GameDataProviderPort`, `EncounterReaderPort`, …)
3. Adapter tests: D1 mappings, EA fixtures sanitized, Queue idempotency
4. Integration: two-organization isolation
5. E2E when Start/Workers are wired

## Required

- Replays of sync/confirm/outbox do not duplicate effects
- Only approved official results change statistics/public projections
- `UNIQUE(provider_key, external_id)` enforced
- Domain/application never import React, Better Auth, Wrangler bindings, or Sentry
